Can I find love?

Or should I marry my late nights

Spent fine tuning madness

Letting my eggs dance to their death?

Is there something wrong with me 
For the way I resist 
The privilege given to me

To pass safely
To be easy
For other people
To digest?

No. I am not a food. 
But if I were, I would be a feast. 
A bacchanal.

I am naturally divergent
Historically divergent

If the genetic buck stops here
I think my great grandmothers ghost would say
“Yes we did it.
You’re it. 
You get to spend your life 
Not propagating
But celebrating 
what our lineage has done 
What our lineage has given the world!”

Those greek party girls 
Blessing America 
Parading in sequins
And passing as women
Of this stolen land
While hushing the secret seed 
Of intersex, 
Transgender 
Gods.

I’m dating my leather 
And the signs I slept on.

I’m in love with my friends 
And the art they inspire in seconds. 

I am parented by the sobering sun that comes through a window in Brooklyn unlike anywhere else in the world. 

The high I get from performing, your applause, my tequila drank- that’s my side b$tch and her partner is cool with it. 

I am married to the way I am constantly changing and learning how to communicate my nuances and depths, 

Married to settling for nothing less than that back. 

I am a father to my sweet Julietta and forever indebted to her auntie when I travel 

To be reminded of all these things. 

That some friends are lovers, 
Some lovers are friends,
Some love is allotted for either or neither 

An excess for exes and ex-enemies. 

At the end of the day this life is a love story you get to write 

So be intentional with who you give your energy to, 

And listen when your nervous system hums to the tune of home. 

(Through the eyes of my king witness, @theemmaexperience )

Tag your lovers and friends and lovers.

Remember that pride is all year 
That pride is intersectional 
That pride is Pro Black 
Pro Trans 
And inclusive of all marginalized identities. 
Let’s keep learning how to be in support of our diverse community by looking beyond the rainbows and drag brunches on Sunday in June.

It’s a risk to get on a stage or even an online platform and tell the world who you are and what you value in such a divisive time and I’m so proud of the wonderful teams of people that rocked with me through every huge pride in America this year. 

We did this INDIE 1000 and I couldn’t be a more proud Dad.

This body, so astounding

Tricks of pleasure 

Pain 

Electric. 

Sometimes I think of how nice it would be to abandon it. 

To be perceived for what I say, create and how I love. 

To relinquish its cravings for toxins 

Its masochism

Its gluttony for adrenaline 

And its disdain for dry heat 

But then I think

Of the humming bird race car that drives through me 

When it’s touched by a welcomed hand

Or the cadence of its sleep

a slow melting stick of butter

Or the summer humidity of New York 

that wraps around it and lulls beads of 

sweat to the upper lip 

Scapulae, 

Knees, 

Salt on my 

Teeth 

My 

teeth 

This body is a collaboration 

A liaison between my mind and 

My world

An imperfect translator

Whom I love 

Like my own. 

@theemmaexperience

Watched showgirls for the first time last night. 

How did I skip this movie entirely and still end up living that life? 

I used to be so afraid of women’s bodies. 

A picture like this would send a hot flash of shame through every cylinder

And I would curse the blasphemy of it all

“How TACKY”

I must have known that these bodies are powerful, 

As powerful as heaven and hell

Must have feared the power of a woman in general

And the inevitable course my life would take to serve her.

It’s wild to know first hand, the depths a person will go to repress their own desires 

Joy

Truth. 

Shame is a cancer. 

And while there is a lot of bad choreography in the movie 

There is also @ginagershon 

(Paving the way for half of the characters I’ve had the pleasure of playing)

With the unparalleled slink of her Cheshire-like spread,

More provocative than any spread Eagle in the film- 

And it’s the smile of a person who knows their power cannot be compromised by the even the cheapest interpretation-

After all she is brave to give her image to you 

Knowing you may be too weak 

With fear 

To worship 

As you should. 

-@katcunning

So excited to be joining @sumofusfest as not a pop star, but a doctor. 

(Jk I am only a doctor when jet blue makes me choose a prefix and I refuse to gender myself), BUT I won’t be singing! 

I’ll be leading a workshop called Oral Hxstories which I crafted to celebrate how we as Trans and Queer people of intersectional identities tell our own stories unlike any other human or robot could! The double entendre welcomes all stories, but the pun is intended if you want to honor your seggsual history while we write, speak, sing or move to calcify and honor some of the nuances we carry in our bodies and don’t always get to see reflected in the world. 

So excited to make memories witcha. ❤️

The schedule is up now! Sep 14-17 in Pinecrest CA. 

Hope to see you at this incredible community moment.

👨‍⚕️ ,
Dr. K Daddy

On Bey Day, 
(while at home healing)

I thought of Beyoncé’s ‘Beyoncé’ and how it made me want to be a pop
Star 
In the costume of a woman 
Who is soft inside the steel bones of her corset as her voice cuts 
sharp
through Capezio mesh.

As you’d guess,
I can’t move much inside my surgical binder, or breathe or run or even sing and laugh as loud as I want because I 
traded those resilient 
whale bones, 
to heal into 
my own.

Took off the exoskeleton but the body can still be a cage 

It’s strange 
That these soft little wounds are mine to dress 
Not in diamonds, Swarovski, in drag or largesse, 
But this chest, in the dull sheen of Vaseline, 
gauze
Just might be the most Bey of all, 
Because, 
soon I’ll wake up ~*Flawless*~ 
with two king bee stings

So as Renaissance plays
And the whole country sings,

Someone put me to sleep 
Let the Energy Move 
It’s a kiss, it’s a bruise 
My new Scorpio 
grooves.

That first taste of being loved, seen and desired for exactly who you are can be so magical, the liaison of that feeling might as well be an angel. 

We face ourselves with such tilting fear we might as well have seen a ghost. 

I wrote this song for the people who dream of or relish in that moment when everything clicks and shame takes no part in the eventuation of even our most curious proclivities. 

Keep your eyes peeled and your knees knelt…

Music Video premiere of ‘Bedroom Angel’ by @katcunning 

As a queer human being, Kat is no stranger to the barren feeling of isolation, but their familiarity in those emotional areas have turned that landscape into a sandbox for them, a place from which they create. Their creations, built with pieces of memory, become shelters of the heart, creating a home for those who have felt isolated, a landscape mapped in the hearts’s lone dreams, fears, and shames. Kat told us, “I think often about the early life of queer people and (anyone who feels ostracized by their immediate community). How olympian our imaginations become in an effort to seek guidance and acceptance, as we create safe havens before we can find them. Our prayers for acceptance are heard somewhere in the zeitgeist of a million other whispers and if we are lucky or determined or a mixture of the two we inch in the physical world toward a person who awakens that first taste of validation, mirroring and of course arousal of what we have always known. That first taste of being loved, seen and desired for exactly who you are can be so magical, the liaison of that feeling might as well be an angel. We face ourselves with such tilting fear we might as well have seen a ghost. I wrote this song for the people who dream of or relish in that moment when everything clicks and shame takes no part in the eventuation of even our most curious proclivities.” Kat previously performed in Cirque Du Soleil, The Deuce (HBO), and is currently playing Reina Reign in Issa Rae’s Rap Sh!t, released on HBO.

I used to find it peculiar that people would want to adorn a costume or use a prop to achieve intimacy. As a young person I was averse to most things that excited me in a way I was ashamed of. I’m lucky that my career as a dancer, which led me to music, which led me to acting, which brings me back to the heart of storytelling every time, has opened my eyes at every step to the power of play. In kink and BDSM spaces- in every nuanced form of drag in life, clothes and props and roles we play can be more of a “shedding” than a “putting on.” Shedding what our society deems we are through oppressively narrow lenses, we widen the apperature to see the most grand potentials of our being. Sometimes the largest version of life can bring us to our most intimate truths. With this video I wanted to honor those communities and experiences that have led me to keep expressing and discovering myself without fear or shame. 

Im so grateful to everyone on this team who took my less articulate texts about this song, and said- “yes I’m down to make an angel a gimp- yes we should set this in a church- yes I will come the day of the shoot wearing black and give you life” 

Because at this stage of my career it is all done on those whims. Without too many cooks in the kitchen I said I wanted to reflect the way NY art scenes, nightlife, history and seggs positive spaces have served as a source of healing trauma and bringing catharsis to my life. They have led me to feel empowered as the person I am, and in the reflection of the people I love so dearly who live boldly in and out of their fantasies, my sense of self, and the celebration of things that were once condemned, is emboldened. 

I wanted to give a taste of that true perspective to you. Permission to play. Permission to imagine. Permission to listen to that ghost when it whispers you dirty little things. 

By the grace of all these bedroom angels, I am so proud to share this with you.
